  "text": "In the absence of intervention our model assumes an age-specific attack rate that is higher in children and young adults (see Methods section), which is consistent with A/H1N1 2009 influenza [CITATION_1] . Previous modelling studies, such as prior work by the authors with the same simulation model used here (see [CITATION_2] supplementary info), and others [CITATION_3] , have found that, as might be expected, school closure is less effective in the case of uniform age-specific attack rates.",
